							case 366:
								break;
							case 367:
								text2 = "La tua rivoluzione";
								text = "Against the background of changes that are increasingly embracing Europe, changes are taking place not only in the East, but also in the West. They do not bypass our western neighbor Italy. Thus, the Italian Socialist Party, headed by Bettino Craxi, which is now in the ruling coalition on the sidelines, plans to take over the entire left Italian political field and create a front of «Social Unity», which will be able to entice a large number of supporters of the PCI, torn by the confrontation of the «neo-Stalinist» and «right» wings of the party. Of course, they are now headed by a young reformist candidate Akille Okketo, a direct protege of the last Secretary General, but it is not clear how he will turn the party further. At the same time, active police measures are continuing against the remnants of the Red Brigades, whose leadership announced the self-dissolution of the organization last year. It is possible for us to have some influence on the degradation of the communist idea in Italy that is taking place now, but does it make sense, against the background of much bigger problems inside our own country?";
								break;
							case 368:
								text2 = "Northern League";
								text = "Against the backdrop of a left-wing decline, local separatism and autonomism are rising in Italy, most pronounced in the «Lombard League» with the charismatic Umberto Bossi, a former member of the Communist Party, which he left because the local Central Committee ignored Lombard identity issues. Despite some marginality, in general, they advocate the federalization of Italy and its greater decentralization, which is increasingly supported by ordinary citizens of predominantly northern regions, who are actually forced to pay for the development of the Italian south. It is noteworthy that they are in favor of the rights of national minorities, including the Italian Slovenes, one way or another oppressed at the moment by Rome. If we wanted, we could get in touch with the «League» and give them some support, but is the game worth the candle?";
								break;
							case 369:
								text2 = "Publication of operation «Gladio»";
								text = "Interesting news comes from Italy. Prime Minister Giulio Andreotti, in a public interview, acknowledged the existence of Operation Gladio, according to which Italian troops, along with the CIA, actively cooperated with a number of right-wing and extremist organizations against communists and left-wing politicians. According to the minister, a number of Italian military men joined in 1964 the Allied Secret Committee, created in 1957 by the United States, France, Belgium and Greece, and which was responsible for directing Gladio operations. A list of 622 civilians directly involved in the work on this operation was also published. After that, Andreotti declared that all weapons caches prepared in case of a Soviet invasion were destroyed, and at the same time said that Gladio was not involved in any of the terrorist attacks in Italy. The Soviet Union is still silent and does not comment on what happened, like most other socialist countries. But how will Yugoslavia react to this news?";
								text = "Interesting news is coming from Italy. In a public interview, Prime Minister Giulio Andreotti acknowledged the existence of Operation Gladio, according to which Italian troops, together with the CIA, actively cooperated with a number of right-wing and extremist organizations against communists and leftist politicians. According to the minister, a number of Italian military joined the Secret Allied Committee in 1964, created in 1957 by the United States, France, Belgium and Greece, and which was responsible for directing Gladio operations. A list of 622 civilians who were directly involved in the work on this operation was also published. After that, Andreotti said that all the weapons caches prepared in case of a Soviet invasion had been destroyed, and at the same time said that Gladio was not involved in any of the terrorist acts in Italy. The Soviet Union is still silent and does not comment on what happened, like most other socialist countries. But how will he react to this news";
								if (this.global1.data[0] == 49 || this.global1.data[0] == 50 || this.global1.data[0] == 51)
